textString: Tokuma Shoten, Studio Ghibli, Nippon Television Network, Buena Vista Home Entertainment, Hakuhodo, Mitsubishi and Toho Present If you find yourself troubled by something mysterious...
or a problem that's hard to solve...
there's a place you can go...
Why bother to set your alarm clock?
Yet the mountains and rivers remain.
The castle draped in the dense greens of spring.
You don't have time to sneak in.
The Cat Returns I hate this.
Late again and embarrassed in front of the whole class.
Machida-kun was laughing at me too.
Well, this must be a sign.
Something even worse is about to begin.
He seems to have a girlfriend.
She's a freshman and very good-looking.
In case you get dumped I'm ready to console you.
Thank you for saving me from a dangerous situation.
I hope you haven't injured yourself.
Please excuse me, but I really must be going now.
Allow me to express my gratitude later.
Never mind, a cat's life is more important.
I can't decide which pattern to use.
Come to think of it, you said so before.
When you were very small, you used to say "I can talk with cats."
Remember I asked you what did you talk about with the cat?
Then you said, "She told me it's tough to make a living in this world."
and I thought it was so funny.
Anyway, I'll get up early tomorrow in time for breakfast.
The King of the Kingdom of Cats.
The cat you saved today was the son of the King, Prince Lune.
Given the importance of the matter, the King himself has come to show his gratitude.
From tomorrow, countless joys will befall you.
It really wasn't you who did this?
It was those cats that did this.
Was it a mistake to save a cat?
Did you get rid of the catnip smell?
It seems OK and the cats aren't after me anymore.
Say, can I ask you a favor?
Can you take my turn for clean-up?
Tsuge-chan has a game today and I can't make it if I don't leave right now.
What on earth am I doing here?
One thing after another all morning.
This project has been taken on by the whole kingdom to express our maximum gratitude!
I don't like cattails or catnip.
How shall I report to the King?
To tell the truth, a lot happened to me recently.
Even a beautiful lady like Haru-sama has troubles.
We'll do our best to make you satisfied.
Please come visit us in the Kingdom of Cats.
Lots of natural scenery and good food.
The whole Kingdom will welcome Haru-sama.
The King is expecting Prince Lune, who you saved yesterday, to welcome Haru-sama as his bride.
He is a cat, but he's cool!
A kingdom of cats might be good.
Eat tons of great food, then have a nap.
Even if he is a prince, that's...
Well then, we'll come for you tonight.
Wait, give me time to think.
That is to say... in a word...
I'm sure those cats will do it.
They'll take me to the Kingdom of Cats.
They'll make me the cat's bride.
What is the Cat Business Office?
A large white cat at the Crossroad will show you the way.
Haru-chan, go to the Crossroad and find the Cat Business Office.
Never heard of the Cat Business Office.
Might be a nice white cat.
Do you know the Cat Business Office?
I mistook you for a different person...
I'm sorry I sat on you.
Hey, isn't there an easier way?
These cats are taking me to their kingdom!
Cut the theatrics and just come out!
Welcome to the Cat Business Office!
This place is in a dimension a little different from yours, a world for beings who have souls.
When people create something with all their heart and hopes, the creation is given a soul, like me and him.
Baron, it's quite rare for you to have a visitor.
Yes, and a quite charming one, don't you think?
The person who created me named me so.
So that's why you're called Baron.
Trouble with some cats from the Cat Kingdom?
I saved a cat from being run over.
Now they're saying, in return, they want to take me to their kingdom.
Too kind for your own good.
Your mind is nasty as ever.
You can't appreciate the kindness which saved a cat.
And she is in trouble for it, right?
Never mix in somebody else's business.
Where did you meet this girl?
She already knew about this place.
Uh, I heard a voice, though I don't know who it was.
You listened to some strange voice?!
Why don't you hold your tongue!
Don't you even know I'm a crow?
Come out from the dark, you fowl!
Nobody can miss a giant marshmallow like you!
You big hog of a cat!
Now, do come in and have a seat.
Any lemon or milk with your tea?
Can't guarantee the flavor though, it's different each time.
How can you drink green leaves?
Too refined for your tongue, I bet.
Tell me about the Kingdom of Cats again.
That whole place is fake, a place for those who don't have a mind of their own.
One of the Cat King's men said they want me to marry their Prince...
I did want to visit the Kingdom of Cats once.
This might be a good opportunity.
But I think I'll give it a miss.
You're not taking her, are you?
But I can't leave her here all alone.
Um, I think I'll go home.
I'm just making trouble for all of you.
I have to solve this myself.
I'm sorry I couldn't be of any help.
I'll just hang around for a while.
Haru, you can come back now.
Muta complains a lot, but doesn't actually mean it.
Note: "Bu" is a reference to his overweight You said it on purpose, didn't you?!
I'm sorry, it wasn't on purpose!
No way I am going to help!
Didn't we have some delicious chiffon cake in the cupboard?
Let's have a piece before we start.
I'll go get my special mulberries then!
It seems like this is going to be fun.
Haru, you need to think about how you can learn to be yourself.
Then, you should have nothing to fear.
I'm putting some whipped cream on top.
Is that Toto-san at the door?
Haru-sama, we have come for you.
Baron, horde of cats headed this way.
Haru-sama, we looked all over for you!
I am going back, this instant!
You must be having pre-marriage blues.
Things got a bit out of hand.
Hey, you, wait, ouch, let go!
Why did we get out of the way!
This is over the weight limit!
This is the Kingdom of Cats?
Well, this is their kingdom, you know.
Ahh, it's so nice and relaxing here.
We should find a way out and go back.
You must go back at once.
Even the cats are prettier here.
Please, you have no time to lose!
Haru-chan, you are not meant to be here.
Why do you know my name?
I am so relieved to find you.
Seems we dropped you when coming in.
Your servant exceeded our weight limit.
A banquet is being prepared in your honor.
You are welcome to join us, Buta-sama.
His Majesty is waiting at the palace.
The palace is right over there.
Maybe it's rude not to greet the King first.
Are you out of your mind?
I serve at the royal table.
So you work at the palace.
Well, I must go see her in person!
Please change before meeting the King.
Please wait in the next room.
Why can't I go in with her?
The dress is very becoming on you.
Prince Lune is the idol of all female cats in this Kingdom.
You'll be very happy with him.
You are the purrfect bride for Lune.
A servant named Buta-sama, I believe.
Um, I am sorry, but I can't really accept marriage to...
I thought you already said yes?
That was what I was told.
He is away at an official function.
Anyway, I don't really know him.
And the Prince, he is a cat, right?
I'm not a cat, so I can't marry him.
That, you don't need to worry about.
He insisted on having a bowl full and dunked himself in catnip jelly.
He didn't have to die like this!
Muta-san, how could you do this to me?
The banquet is ready to begin.
I don't want to leave him.
Then, he will come with us.
She has a perfect pair of ears!
I was told you don't like mice, so I have prepared fresh fish for you.
What do we have for entertainment?
Oh no, I even sound like a cat!
I never felt like this before.
Being a cat might not be that bad.
You must learn to be yourself.
I already told you that, didn't I?
Take His Majesty to a safe place!
Baron, I knew you would come.
I've heard about you and your Office.
If I had listened to you, this wouldn't have happened.
If you leave before dawn, you can still become human.
A secret passage to the outside.
This is the back of the castle.
The top of that tower leads to the exit.
You must go through the ruins to the tower and then climb up.
I haven't even thanked her yet.
Haru, this is just my guess.
But isn't she the one who led you to me?
Yes, that beautiful voice was hers.
Because of you, I almost died.
That labyrinth was built with our state-of-the-art technology.
We'll enjoy the view from here.
The sun is still high, though.
It won't be easy to get out of there.
We have nothing to worry about.
We must keep trying, one by one.
Keep your eyes on the tower.
Why get lost just 'cause it's a maze.
Why does it have to be me?
Let's hurry while he keeps them busy.
Why do I have to be the bait?!
I was going to buy a new one anyway.
There was no wall here a minute ago.
Are you saying that walls have feet?
I told them not to get in line!
I have soldiers waiting in the tower, just in case.
I'm afraid the tower's getting old...
This is not good at all!
We have no choice, but use THAT.
If you do that, Your Majesty, your image will go to shambles.
There is no such thing here.
Yay, we came out to an opening.
Gikkingen-kun, nice to see you again.
We'll go back to the castle right away.
Being a cat is not so bad.
Do I have to learn to like mice?
It's too early to give up.
I hurried back, thanks to Yuki-chan.
Err, I just wanted to thank her.
I thought you'd be happy to have Haru-chan as your bride.
You don't need to worry about me.
I went to your old home to find this.
Oh, could this be what I think it is?
These are the fish cookies you gave me when I was an orphan kitten.
You're so beautiful now that I didn't recognize you.
Will you accept these as a token of our life together from now on?
Oh, I am so happy for you, Yuki-chan!
If I hadn't met you then, I could have starved on the streets.
You also saved me from danger.
I didn't know you were the person Yuki told me so much about.
You saved both of our lives.
You two made me so happy already.
Saving a cat was a good thing.
This is such a moving sight.
So you already had a fianc?
